Element_Description: Quality Element under the Understandability Dimension. Evaluates language requirements (specification of language, English available..).
Quality Element evaluating the service's robustness.
Data absent from the dataset, as described by the scope [ISO 19157-1:2021].
Excess data present in the dataset, as described by the scope [ISO 19157-1:2021].
Closeness of the value of a quantitative attribute to a value accepted as or known to be true [ISO 19157-1:2021].
Correctness of non-quantitative attributes is correct or incorrect [ISO 19157-1:2021].
Comparison of the classes assigned to features or their attributes to a universe of discourse [ISO 19157-1:2021].
Adherence to rules of the conceptual schema [ISO 19157-1:2021].
Adherence of values to the value domains [ISO 19157-1:2021].
Degree to which data are stored in accordance with the physical structure of the dataset, as described by the scope [ISO 19157-1:2021].
Refers to the property of a set of geometric objects or transformations that preserve their relative position or shape.
Correctness of the explicitly encoded topological characteristics of the dataset as described by the scope [ISO 19157-1:2021].
Closeness of reported time measurements to values accepted as true [ISO 19157-1:2021].
Evaluates the correctness of the order of events [ISO 19157-1:2021].
Validity of data with respect to time. [ISO 19157-1:2021].
Closeness of reported coordinate values to values accepted as true in a standard coordinate reference system [ISO 19157-1:2021].
Closeness of the relative positions of features in the scope to their respective relative positions accepted as true in a local coordinate reference system [ISO 19157-1:2021].
Closeness of gridded data position values to values accepted as true [ISO 19157-1:2021].
